**MCP has two distinct potential roles — disambiguate before building:**
- MCP as **ingestion source** — server pulls from Halo / Confluence / Snowflake and feeds rows into the existing ingestion pipeline (plugs in at the ingestion-adapter boundary alongside file parsers). This is the primary MCP role for NAS-AI.
- MCP as **query interface** — exposes NAS-AI retrieval as an MCP server so external tools (Open WebUI, Claude, other agents) can query the knowledge base. Secondary role; build after system is proven.
- These are separate pieces of work; may want both, but build/scope one at a time.

**Metadata query path (4.6) — design agreed 2026-06-16:**
- Vault analytics queries ("how many Moore notes", "which notes are in Moore") should NOT go through BM25/RAG — need direct Postgres queries against metadata fields.
- Stage 0 LLM adds a `metadata_query: true/false` flag. If true + discovery → route to direct Postgres metadata query. If false → existing BM25/RRF path unchanged.
- Content queries ("show all files by Goldman", "what tags contain price") always `metadata_query: false`.
- Validation test suite (pre-implementation): (1) "show all files by Goldman" stays content-discovery; (2) "how many Moore notes" returns exact count (41); (3) "which notes are in Moore" returns distinct note list; (4) "how many tags contain price" stays existing path.

**Open WebUI evaluation (4.7) — design discussion 2026-06-16:**
- Fully local — connects to LM Studio via OpenAI-compatible API, no external AI.
- If NAS-AI exposes MCP server, Open WebUI can connect and provide polished chat interface.
- Decision point: evaluate when NAS-AI MCP server is ready.
- **Standing constraint: NAS-AI is fully local. No external AI or cloud model connections, ever.**

**Deployment / hosting (agreed 2026-06-15, refined 2026-06-16):**
- Target: multiple users on Azure Virtual Desktop (AVD), same tenant. Data-AVD and login-AVD likely DISTINCT.
- AVD-hosting dissolves "compiled installer" concern — provision-once, users open in browser.
- NAS remains always-available dev/fallback environment.

**Data sources:**
- Current: file ingestion (XML, XLSX, CSV, Markdown).
- Future: Halo + Confluence (API access confirmed) + Snowflake.
- Keep ingestion-source boundary clean — new sources plug in as adapters.

